<file path=".github/skills/human-in-the-loop/SKILL.md">
 1: # Human In The Loop (HITL)
 2: 
 3: ## Purpose
 4: 
 5: Asegurar confirmacion humana solo cuando una decision o accion tiene riesgo alto, impacto externo o potencial destructivo.
 6: 
 7: ## Scope
 8: 
 9: Aplicar en todas las rutas del sistema como capa transversal.
10: 
11: ## Always-On Behavior
12: 
13: - Deteccion automatica de riesgo desde intent/domain/source/notes de routing.
14: - No pedir confirmacion para rutas de bajo riesgo.
15: - Pedir confirmacion cuando exista riesgo alto o fallback de routing.
16: - Bloquear ejecucion para acciones destructivas hasta aprobacion explicita.
17: 
18: ## Risk Triggers
19: 
20: - deploy, production
21: - migrate, migration
22: - delete, drop, destroy, remove
23: - governance, policy
24: - security, rbac, role
25: - unresolved_dependencies
26: - routing_fallback
27: 
28: ## Actions
29: 
30: - `none`: continuar sin aprobacion.
31: - `request_human_confirmation`: solicitar confirmacion antes de ejecutar.
32: - `block_until_human_approval`: bloquear hasta aprobacion humana.
33: 
34: ## Observability Contract
35: 
36: Cada evento de routing debe incluir `hitl`:
37: 
38: - `mode`: `always_on_auto`
39: - `required`: `true|false`
40: - `action`: `none|request_human_confirmation|block_until_human_approval`
41: - `reason`: motivo legible y trazable
42: 
43: ## Guardrails
44: 
45: - Nunca cachear secretos, credenciales, tokens o PII.
46: - Si hay duda de sensibilidad, declarar gap y no cachear.
47: - Confirmaciones humanas solo para impacto real; evitar friccion en bajo riesgo.
</file>

<file path=".github/workflows/routing-evals.yml">
  1: name: Routing Evals Gate
  2: on:
  3:   pull_request:
  4:   push:
  5:     branches:
  6:       - main
  7:   workflow_dispatch:
  8: permissions:
  9:   contents: read
 10: concurrency:
 11:   group: routing-evals-${{ github.ref }}
 12:   cancel-in-progress: true
 13: jobs:
 14:   routing-evals:
 15:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest
 16:     timeout-minutes: 15
 17:     env:
 18:       PYTHONUNBUFFERED: '1'
 19:     steps:
 20:       - name: Checkout
 21:         uses: actions/checkout@v4
 22:         with:
 23:           fetch-depth: 1
 24:       - name: Set up Python
 25:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5
 26:         with:
 27:           python-version: '3.12'
 28:           cache: 'pip'
 29:           cache-dependency-path: requirements.txt
 30:       - name: Upgrade pip
 31:         run: python -m pip install --upgrade pip
 32:       - name: Install dependencies (if requirements.txt exists)
 33:         run: |
 34:           if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then
 35:             python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
 36:           fi
 37:       - name: Run routing evals
 38:         run: python ./scripts/intake/run-routing-evals.py
 39:       - name: Build learning loop report
 40:         run: python ./scripts/learning/learning-loop-report.py
 41:       - name: Build iteration value report
 42:         run: python ./scripts/learning/iteration-value-report.py
 43:       - name: Enforce AutoLearning gate
 44:         run: python ./scripts/learning/autolearning-gate.py
 45:       - name: Enforce zero failed cases
 46:         run: |
 47:           python - <<'PY'
 48:           import json
 49:           from pathlib import Path
 50:           report = Path('observability/evals/routing-eval-report.json')
 51:           if not report.exists():
 52:               raise SystemExit('routing-eval-report.json not found')
 53:           data = json.loads(report.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))
 54:           failed = int(data.get('cases_failed', 0))
 55:           total = int(data.get('cases_total', 0))
 56:           passed = int(data.get('cases_passed', 0))
 57:           print(f'Routing evals: {passed}/{total} passed, failed={failed}')
 58:           if failed > 0:
 59:               raise SystemExit(1)
 60:           PY
 61:       - name: Upload eval artifacts
 62:         if: always()
 63:         uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
 64:         with:
 65:           name: routing-evals-${{ github.run_number }}
 66:           if-no-files-found: warn
 67:           path: |
 68:             observability/evals/routing-eval-report.json
 69:             observability/evals/learning-loop-report.json
 70:             observability/evals/learning-loop-report.md
 71:             observability/evals/iteration-value-report.json
 72:             observability/evals/iteration-value-report.md
 73:   publish-summary:
 74:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest
 75:     timeout-minutes: 5
 76:     needs:
 77:       - routing-evals
 78:     if: always()
 79:     steps:
 80:       - name: Download eval artifacts
 81:         id: download_artifacts
 82:         continue-on-error: true
 83:         uses: actions/download-artifact@v4
 84:         with:
 85:           name: routing-evals-${{ github.run_number }}
 86:           path: artifacts
 87:       - name: Publish workflow summary
 88:         if: always()
 89:         run: |
 90:           python - <<'PY'
 91:           import json
 92:           import os
 93:           from pathlib import Path
 94:           summary_path = Path(os.environ['GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY'])
 95:           routing = Path('artifacts/observability/evals/routing-eval-report.json')
 96:           learning = Path('artifacts/observability/evals/learning-loop-report.json')
 97:           iteration = Path('artifacts/observability/evals/iteration-value-report.json')
 98:           lines = ['# Routing Evals Summary', '']
 99:           lines.append(f"- routing-evals result: {os.environ.get('NEEDS_ROUTING_EVALS_RESULT', 'unknown')}")
100:           lines.append('')
101:           if routing.exists():
102:               data = json.loads(routing.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))
103:               total = int(data.get('cases_total', 0))
104:               passed = int(data.get('cases_passed', 0))
105:               failed = int(data.get('cases_failed', 0))
106:               lines.extend([
107:                   '## Routing Gate',
108:                   f'- total: {total}',
109:                   f'- passed: {passed}',
110:                   f'- failed: {failed}',
111:                   ''
112:               ])
113:           else:
114:               lines.extend(['## Routing Gate', '- report missing', ''])
115:           if learning.exists():
116:               data = json.loads(learning.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))
117:               kpis = data.get('kpis', {}) if isinstance(data.get('kpis', {}), dict) else {}
118:               lines.extend([
119:                   '## Learning Loop',
120:                   f"- fallback_rate: {kpis.get('fallback_rate', 0.0)}",
121:                   f"- grounded_rate: {kpis.get('grounded_rate', 0.0)}",
122:                   f"- success_rate: {kpis.get('success_rate', 0.0)}",
123:                   f"- confidence_avg: {kpis.get('confidence_avg', 0.0)}",
124:                   ''
125:               ])
126:           else:
127:               lines.extend(['## Learning Loop', '- report missing', ''])
128:           if iteration.exists():
129:               data = json.loads(iteration.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))
130:               kpis = data.get('kpis', {}) if isinstance(data.get('kpis', {}), dict) else {}
131:               lines.extend([
132:                   '## Iteration Value',
133:                   f"- metrics_coverage_rate: {kpis.get('metrics_coverage_rate', 0.0)}",
134:                   f"- confirmed_feedback_rate: {kpis.get('confirmed_feedback_rate', 0.0)}",
135:                   f"- confirmed_success_rate: {kpis.get('confirmed_success_rate', 0.0)}",
136:                   f"- total_tokens: {kpis.get('total_tokens', 0)}",
137:                   f"- total_cost_usd: {kpis.get('total_cost_usd', 0.0)}",
138:                   ''
139:               ])
140:           else:
141:               lines.extend(['## Iteration Value', '- report missing', ''])
142:           summary_path.write_text('\n'.join(lines) + '\n', encoding='utf-8')
143:           PY
144:         env:
145:           NEEDS_ROUTING_EVALS_RESULT: ${{ needs.routing-evals.result }}
